# la/tarot.ftl — Latin (Latina) translation
#
# Status: DRAFT — MEDIUM-HIGH CONFIDENCE on Major Arcana, MEDIUM on Minor
# Arcana suits. Tarot's Renaissance Italian roots provide direct Latin
# lineage for most Major Arcana names: Stultus (Fool), Praestigiator
# (Magician), Papissa (High Priestess), Imperatrix/Imperator
# (Empress/Emperor), Pontifex (Hierophant), Mors (Death), Diabolus (Devil),
# Mundus (World). Minor Arcana suits use the classical Italian-Latin
# convention: Calices/Gladii/Baculi/Denarii. Court ranks add Eques (Knight)
# — well-attested classical Latin.
#
# Schema note: this file follows the en-US `name-rank-tarot-special-` prefix
# for Major Arcana (matching the corrected de/tarot.ftl after the
# 2026-04-29 schema fix).
#
# Needs: a Latinist with Renaissance Tarot familiarity for promotion. The
# Hanged Man (Suspensus), Hermit (Eremita), and Wheel of Fortune (Rota
# Fortunae) have multiple attested forms; current choices follow the most
# direct medieval Latin conventions.

